em comentário mas tem Framework ou Sistemas que pede isso, bom simples.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Localize o arquivo &lt;em&gt;php.ini&lt;/em&gt; no seu servidor e ache a linha 
&lt;em&gt;date.timezone.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Pronto agroa coloque ele assim:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;date&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;timezone&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;America/Sao_Paulo&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Pronto, agora de um restart no seu HTTPD (Apache) e já esta funcionando.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="date"></category><category term="date.timezone"></category><category term="php"></category><category term="timezone"></category></entry></feed>